[SN]TITLE[SN]
'Gunfire' probe as road in Aberdeen closed for six hours

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A report of gunfire in an Aberdeen street is being investigated by police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Officers were called to Provost Rust Drive at 22:30 on Wednesday after reports that a firearm may have been discharged near the junction with North Anderson Drive and Moir Crescent.
The road was only reopened more than six hours later at 04:40.
Police Scotland said nobody was injured and appealed for anyone who saw or heard anything suspicious to get in touch.
